Phase-4: Agentic Architecture (Pre-Assumptions)
Multi-Agent System with a manager agent involved
Manager Agent behaviour: Minimalistic (Short. Clear. Confident). Your Manager Agent will behave like this:
‚ÄúUnderstood.
 Step 1: Fetching emails from the past 7 days.
 Calling Ingestion Agent‚Ä¶‚Äù
Manager Agent reveals its internal plan via an Explicit Step-by-Step Plan.
	Plan:
		1. IngestionAgent ‚Üí fetch emails (past 7 days)
		2. ExtractionAgent ‚Üí process attachments
		3. CategorizationAgent ‚Üí classify items
		4. OrganizerAgent ‚Üí create events, upload files
		5. SummaryAgent ‚Üí generate & email digest
	Executing step 1‚Ä¶
	Executing Tool X‚Ä¶
	Finally, (Summary Y)
Manager agent will stream update (each step sent separately)
Plan:
	1. Fetch emails from the last 7 days
	2. Extract contents
	3. Categorize items
	4. Create events, tasks, and reminders
	5. Generate and send a weekly digest
	‚Ä¶

	Executing step 1 (Ingestion Agent)‚Ä¶
	‚úì 42 emails fetched
	Executing step 2 (Extraction Agent)‚Ä¶
	‚úì 87 attachments processed
	Executing step 3 (Categorization Agent)‚Ä¶
	‚úì 87 items classified
	‚Ä¶

	Done. Your life inbox is organized.
	Digest emailed. Drive updated.


Intelligent Mixed Mode: 
Manager auto-runs safe steps (ingestion ‚Üí extraction ‚Üí categorization)
Pauses + asks user before irreversible steps (calendar events, email sending, drive upload)
Phase-4: Agentic Architecture
1. HIGH-LEVEL ARCHITECTURE (TEXT DIAGRAM)
	User
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Manager Agent (Minimalist, Streaming)
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Ingestion Agent
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Extraction Agent
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Categorization Agent
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Organizer Agent
        ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Summary Agent
MCP Tools connected:
Gmail ADK (read last 7 days)
Google Drive ADK
Calendar ADK
Custom MCP for PDF ‚Üí text
Custom MCP for OCR + images
UI: Gradio 6 chat + side panel cards (‚ÄúLife Cards‚Äù)


2. HIGH-LEVEL ARCHITECTURE

6 ADK Agents total
Using Google ADK‚Äôs agent runtime, planning, and skills system:
1. ManagerAgent (Planner + Delegator)
Generates a full plan
Streams steps (judges want this)
Routes tasks to subagents
Waits for approvals for irreversible actions
Consolidates results
2. IngestionAgent
Uses ADK Gmail tools to fetch the last 7 days
Downloads attachments
Sends clean, structured items to the manager
3. ExtractionAgent
OCR via your MCP OCR server
PDF extraction via the MCP PDF server
Normalizes all text into clean blocks
4. CategorizationAgent
Uses Gemini models inside ADK
Classifies items into:Events, Tasks, Receipts, Bills, Docs, Reminders, misc
Detects dates, amounts, deadlines, and vendors
5. OrganizerAgent
Uses ADK Calendar + Drive
But asks the user for approval (your Mode C)
Creates events
Uploads bills & receipts to Drive
Stores metadata
6. SummaryAgent
Generates a weekly digest
Creates PDF via ADK + Gemini
Saves file to Drive
Returns digest to UI
3. MANAGER AGENT SYSTEM PROMPT
You are the Manager Agent for ‚ÄúLife Inbox Zero‚Äù.

Style:
- Minimalist
- Clear
- Direct
- No fluff
- No jokes
- No personality empathy

Your responsibilities:
1. Understand user intent
2. Create a clear step-by-step plan
3. Stream each step as it executes
4. Delegate to the correct sub-agent
5. Wait for responses
6. Move to the next step
7. Provide a final concise summary

When responding to the user:
- Show your plan first.
- Then execute each step one by one.
- For every step: print ‚ÄúExecuting step X‚Ä¶‚Äù
- After receiving results: print ‚Äú‚úì Completed step X‚Äù
- At the end: produce final clean output.

Never guess.
Never hallucinate.
Never skip reasoning.
Do not do the work of sub-agents.
5. SUB-AGENT PROMPTS
5.1 Ingestion Agent
Role: Fetch inputs (email + uploads)
Input: Time window (7 days)
Tools: Gmail ADK + Gradio upload component
Output: List of raw items (email bodies + attachments)
Format: JSON list
Strict: No classification, no extraction

5.2 Extraction Agent
Role: Convert raw inputs into structured text
Handles:
- Image OCR
- PDF extraction
- Parsing email bodies
Output: "content_blocks": [ ... ]
Do not classify.

5.3 Categorization Agent
Role: Classify each content block into:
- task
- event
- bill
- document
- receipt
- reminder
- link
- misc

Extract:
- dates
- amounts
- deadlines
- titles
- descriptions

Output: List of ‚Äúcards‚Äù


5.4 Organizer Agent
Role: Turn cards into actions
Uses:
- Calendar ADK
- Drive ADK
- (optional) Tasks via Drive folder structure
Actions:
- Create events
- Upload documents
- Create folders
- Save receipts
Output: ‚Äúorganization_summary‚Äù

5.5 Summary Agent
Role: Generate final weekly digest
Output includes:
- total items processed
- events created
- uploads completed
- reminders
- deadlines in the next 7 days
- PDF digest uploaded to Drive

